Package: macrosyntR
Type: Package
Title: Draw Oxford Grids
Version: 0.2.9
Authors@R: person("Sami", "El Hilali",email = "elhilali.sami@gmail.com", 
  role = c("aut", "cre"),comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4417-8399"))
Maintainer: Sami El Hilali <elhilali.sami@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
  stats,
  utils,
  ggplot2,
  ggthemes,
  igraph,
  tidyr,
  reshape2,
  dplyr
Description: Use standard genomic file format to evaluate pair-wise synteny conservation at the genome-wide scale. 
  It takes a table of orthologs and genome annotation files formatted as BED to automatically infer 
  significantly conserved linkage groups, and order them on an Oxford Grid.
